The paper deals with image processing tasks related to computer vision, specifically shadow detection and removal. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework based on a conditional generative adversarial network, which involves training a generator and a discriminator. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves modeling higher-level relationships and global scene characteristics, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on large-scale datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
